parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of brake lines and hoses can cause brake fluid leaks, leading to a loss of brake pressure, which can result in extended stopping distances, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS brake system can cause the vehicle to take longer to stop, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Unwanted ABS activation at low speeds
extended stopping distances
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness can cause the brake lights to fail, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Brake lights fail to illuminate
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper motor can cause the wipers to malfunction or stop working altogether, leading to reduced visibility during inclement weather, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wipers work intermittently
hesitate to start
stop working suddenly
or continue running after being turned off. The wipers may also work only when the vehicle is not in motion or when the weather is dry.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering wheel position sensor can cause the vehicle to lose power steering, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or wanders
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel jerks or moves on its own
the vehicle is hard to steer
the steering feels like driving on ice.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering pump can cause the vehicle to lose power steering, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Fluid leaking under the vehicle
the steering wheel feels hard to turn
